cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this profile, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Hardware-Aware TLS Identity Binding Profile: Draft v0.1.0"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-06-11"
authors:
  - name: "thinksyncs"
license: "Apache-2.0"
repository-code: "https://github.com/thinksyncs/hardware-aware-tls-identity-binding"
abstract: >-
  A draft security profile for agent-to-agent and other application protocols
  using TLS 1.3, post-handshake platform attestation, session binding,
  Manager-signed Identity Grants, Agent Session Binding Statements, and
  deterministic expected-versus-observed policy checks. AGTP is treated as one
  reference target, not as the owner of the profile.
keywords:
  - AGTP
  - TLS 1.3
  - remote attestation
  - session binding
  - identity binding
  - authorization
  - relay resistance
  - diversion resistance
